snippet.description:
Follow me on Twitter: https://twitter.com/SuperFunToys

This is a Star Wars: The Force Awakens lightsaber toy review and unboxing video for kids! Check out Kylo Ren's lightsaber from the Star Wars episode seven movie! It is a new release toy from 2016 and is a lot of fun. Great video for boys and girls to watch!

Super Fun Toy Channel is the best toy review and unboxing channel for boys, girls and all kids! 
Common Questions asked to the Super Fun Toy Channel:
What is your favorite movie?
I love the Minions from the Minion movie but my favorite movies are superhero movies. I love Batman, Robin, Superman, the Avengers, Hulk, Iron Man, Spiderman, Captain America, Wolverine and Thor. I even like the bad guys and villains like Venom, Doctor Octopus, Carnage, Thanos, Electro, Green Goblin and the Joker. I also like Woody and Buzz Lightyear from Toy Story. I like Pixel Cars toys – like Lightning McQueen, Mater, Sarge, and Francesco Bernoulli. I like Ninja Turtles, Spiderman, Batman, Lego, Play doh, Kinder Surprise Eggs, Peppa Pig and Thomas the Train. I also like Dinosaurs from Jurassic Park.
Paw Patrol toys. These are my favorites in order: Chase, Ryder, Zooma, Rocky, Rubble, Skye and Marshall. Paw Patrol toys rock!!
What are your favorite toys to play with?
So many! I like Pixel Cars toys – like Lightning McQueen, Mater, Sarge, and Francesco Bernoulli. I like Ninja Turtles, Spiderman, Batman, Lego, Play doh, Kinder Surprise Eggs, Peppa Pig and Thomas the Train. I also like Dinosaurs from Jurassic Park. 
What are your favorite boys or girls toys to unbox?
I love opening surprise eggs, especially kinder surprise eggs. My favorite is probably Paw Patrol toys. These are my favorites in order: Chase, Ryder, Zooma, Rocky, Rubble, Skye and Marshall. Paw Patrol toys rock!!
What kind of toys do you use in your videos?
All kinds! Hasbro, Little Tykes, Imaginex, Lego, Playdoh, Marvel, DC, Nickelodeon. I buy most of my toys from Toys R Us and then I donate them to needy families.

snippet.title: LEGO Chima 70146 Flying Phoenix Fire Temple Kids Toy Review & Unboxing
snippet.description:
LEGO Chima 70146 Flying Phoenix Fire Temple Toy Review & Unboxing

It's the ultimate fire vs. ice showdown as the Saber-tooth warriors attack the all-powerful Phoenix tribe's Fire Temple. Can they capture the great Phoenix leader Fluminox and his CHI and take control of the entire Kingdom of Chima? Behind the gates, there's a pool of fire balls and an array of red-hot weaponry to put the heat on the invaders. Help Flinx defend the Temple from the gun turret and unleash the fire bombs. Act quickly before the Saber-tooth vehicle breaks down the Temple walls with its powerful clawing function. Or activate fire CHI power mode to convert part of the temple into a huge flying Phoenix, taking the thrilling action to the sky against the ejected Saber-tooth flyer! 

Includes 7 minifigures with weapons: Fluminox, Flinx, Foltrax, Tormak, Li'Ella, Stealthor and Voom Voom
Phoenix Fire Temple features base opening/closing function, load-and-fire bombing feature, 2 gun turrets with gun sight and seats for minifigures, opening gate, pool of fire balls and translucent flame elements, plus fire CHI power mode flying Phoenix with fire CHI, ball shooters, load-and-fire bombing feature and phoenix detailing
Saber-tooth vehicle features clawing function, CHI, ball shooter, ice fangs, claws and tail plus detachable flyer with posable wings
Weapons include a Wingfurno for Fluminox, Flikker for Flinx, Emberstaf for Foltrax, Tygafyre for Tormak, Roarburn for Li'Ella, Koldstaf for Stealthor and a Double Axicles for Voom Voom
Place Phoenix minifigures in the gun turret seats and target the invaders
Unleash the fire bombs
Enter fire CHI power mode to convert part of the Temple into a flying Phoenix!
Claw the temple wall with the Saber-tooth vehicle
Detach the Saber-tooth flyer and shoot the ice orbs
Phoenix Fire Temple measures over 6" (16cm) high, 17" (44cm) long and 18" (46cm) wide, and over 3" (10cm) high, 15" (39cm) long and 17" (45cm) wide in fire-up mode
2-in-1 Saber-tooth vehicle measures over 6" (16cm) high, 8" (21cm) long and 4" (12cm) wide
Saber-tooth detachable flyer measures over 2" (6cm) high, 9" (23cm) long and 7" (18cm) wide

AMAZON Prograce kids smart watch can tell time, counting steps, taking pictures, FM radio and lot more functions. it has music, you also can open the Bluetooth to listen to music through a Bluetooth headset. Kids also like its flashlight at night. Also four small games, kids can relax when they are tired. I believe that this kids watch is able to help your children to schedule time and bring your children endless happiness.

Features:

⌚ 3D style digital & analogue clock faces
📷Take photos
🎼 Play music
📻 Listen to radio
🎮Built-in Games
👣 Pedometer step counter
🔋 600mAh battery; long working time
⏱Stopwatch
🔦Flashlight

Material: ABS
Screen size: 1.5 inches LCD touch screen
Battery: rechargeable built-in 600mAh
Interface: USB 2.0
Watch body dimension: 5x4x1.4cm / 2x1.6x0.6inch (L*W*H)

Prograce kids smart watch is designed with 1.54" IPS touch screen, audio music player, FM radio, stopwatch, rotatable camera , built-in games, pedometer, calories, flash light, support external earphone; A great birthday / holiday/ Christmas gift for boys and girls.

Can kids easily selfie? 
90° rotatable camera allow your kids to take pictures and selfie with one camera, just adjust the angle, easy for kids to take photos.

Can kids play games? 
Built-in 4 funny and mini games(Whac-A-Mole, Ninja Run Online, Welcome the God of Wealth, Brave Money) in this smart watch, children can play through the touch screen and select the game for their prefer, train them in coordination and thinking in leisure time.

Can kids play music and listen FM Radio? 
You can play the music in the memory card (Card not included) by selecting Audio Play (Note: The music should be copied to My Music file before playing.) You can even plug an earphone and listen to FM radio too. 6-level volume to choose; better sound quality.

snippet.description:
Transformers RID Combiner Force wave 3 has been released! The Transformers Robots in Disguise crash combers are so cool. In this RID comber force brand toy review episode we have crash combiner Dragbreak, who is combiner force of the decepticons Dragestrip and Wildbreak, and Shocknado, who is a combiner force of Shockdrive and Warnado. You can mix them up to create DRAGNADO with dragstrip and warnado and SHOCKBREAK with Shockdrive and Warnado. You can even combine the other Combine Force to make Autobot Decepticon robots to make PrimeDrag and Beeshock and all kinds of other crazy combinations in the Transformer universe. These one step transformer and Robots in disguise are so awesome! Mr Hands got mixed up on the names of Shockdrive and Warnado and Bobby thought it was really funny. Hr Hands needs to learn his Transformer RID name better. Transformers are so much fun to play with and use your imagination to pretend like you are on cartoon network. What happens when you crash and combine forces with Transformers Robots in Disguise Decepticon Shockdrive, Warnado, Dragstrip and Wildbreak figures? No, not a traffic jam. You get an awesome 2-bot Dragbreak Crash Combiner figure. Shocknado combines to send Autobots to their downfall. He electrifies their processors and jolts their systems into overload. All road and no rules makes Dragbreak a devious destructor. He’s a bot bent on wreaking havoc on the roads.
